<\body>
  <tmdoc-title|Special markup for programs>

  The <tmdtd|program> <abbr|d.t.d.> provides markup for the layout of
  computer programs. However, these tags should be considered as very
  unstable, since we plan to replace them by a set of more detailed tags:

  <\explain|<explain-macro|algorithm|name|body>>
    The <src-arg|name> of the algorithm and its <src-arg|body>, which
    includes its possible specification.
  </explain>

  <\explain|<explain-macro|body|body>>
    The real body of the algorithm.
  </explain>

  <\explain|<explain-macro|indent|content>>
    For indenting part of an algorithm.
  </explain>

